# Www pins + feed handoff

## Pins (this silo)

- `.cursor/build-order.md` — product build sequence SoT
- `.cursor/lanes.md` — adopted website lanes + generated Pending proposals
- `.cursor/backlog.md` — www deferred / next requirements (Brian prefs)

Update **build-order + lanes** same turn when plans are created/reordered/Built/shipped or lanes change. Update **backlog** same turn when Brian adds requirements or priority. No hub-work-queue clone — one thin sync script only (below).

## Strategy feed (read-only from www)

Before product planning or lane changes — and whenever Brian asks to look at / check the feed — read:

`/mnt/DataStore/Ventures/project-codex/codex-business/docs/www-feed.md`

### Feed → Pending (automatic — tier C)

1. **Hook (primary):** `.cursor/hooks/www-feed-lanes-sync.sh` runs on Read / beforeReadFile / shell touching `www-feed.md` and applies `scripts/www-lanes-sync.py` (fails open).
2. **Script (manual / resume):** `python3 scripts/www-lanes-sync.py` — rewrite Pending; `--check` exits 1 on drift.
3. Do not hand-edit inside `<!-- www-lanes-sync:begin/end -->` markers.

Feed lane names are **proposals** until adopted into the adopted-lanes table in `lanes.md`. On adopt: move into adopted table, re-run sync (or let the next feed read sync), and note for a business session to mark the feed proposal `adopted in www`.

### Product proposals / Ready (habit-only)

Treat **Product proposals** and **Ready for planning** as intentional handoffs — graduate into www plans when Brian asks. Do **not** mirror a Pending Product proposals table. Do not re-decide from scratch unless blocked. Only Ready (and Brian-authorized proposals) become plan candidates — not backlog stubs.

## Reverse feed (www → business)

Www owns `docs/business-feed.md`. Business reads; www never edits `codex-business/`.

**Same turn** when an event passes the content filter:

| Include | Skip |
|---------|------|
| User/commercial-meaningful **Shipped** | Routine eng noise (refactors, lint, local DX) |
| **Stumbles** hitting cost / rights / timeline / feasibility | Pin housekeeping unless commercially relevant |
| **Learnings** that change money or positioning | |
| **Asks-back** to business | |

Write the matching section + bump Meta + Changelog. Refresh `.cursor/build-order.md` / `lanes.md` when those signals affect pins.

Schema SoT (read-only): `/mnt/DataStore/Ventures/project-codex/codex-business/docs/protocol/dual-feed.md`

## Must not

- Edit `codex-business/` from a www-only workspace (switch silo / Ventures root)
- Treat backlog stubs as Ready — only feed **Ready for planning** items become www plan candidates
- Leave `lanes.md` Pending stale after reading www-feed
- Hand-edit the generated Pending block (use sync / adopt flow)
- Dump routine eng noise into `docs/business-feed.md`
